==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shire horse
<hw>Shire horse</hw>. <def>One of an English breed of heavy draft horses
believed to be descended largely from the horses used in war in the days
of heavy armor. They are the largest of the British draft breeds, and
have long hair on the back of the cannons and fetlocks. Brown or bay
with white on the face and legs is now the commonest color.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

